Exercise 13.51: Although unique_ptrs cannot be copied, in § 12.1.5 (p.
471) we wrote a clone function that returned a unique_ptr by value.
Explain why that function is legal and how it works.

Answer:
In the clone function we return a unique_ptr that is about to be destroyed so the move operation is called instead of the copy operation
and since unique_ptr are able to be moved


Exercise 13.52: Explain in detail what happens in the assignments of the
HasPtr objects on page 541. In particular, describe step by step what
happens to values of hp, hp2, and of the rhs parameter in the HasPtr
assignment operator.

Answer:
In the first assignment, hp = hp2, Copy constructor is called in order to copy hp2 to rhs,after which hp2 will hold
not change and rhs will point to a different string with the same value